article.description: Erik Durham scored 20 points and Jacksonville State held Cal State Fullerton to 14 points in the second half for a 61-38 win at the Global Sports Classic on Friday.
article.headline: Durham's 20 leads Jacksonville State past Fullerton 61-38
article.linkText: Durham's 20 leads Jacksonville State past Fullerton 61-38
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Erik Durham scored 20 points and Jacksonville State held Cal State Fullerton to 14 points in the second half for a 61-38 win at the Global Sports Classic on Friday. Norbertas Giga added 11 points and a career-high 12 rebounds, with Christian Cunningham matching his career high with 12 rebounds for the Gamecocks (3-3), who had a 42-26 advantage on the boards. Jacksonville State led 28-24 at halftime and was only up 40-31 midway through the second half. Durham, who had four of his five 3-pointers in the second half, hit one at 9:50 to start a 21-7 game-closing run. Tre Collins led the Titans (2-3) with 11 points. Fullerton shot 26 percent (10 of 39), making just 4 of 15 3-pointers and grabbing just four offensive rebounds. The Titans only had nine rebounds in the second half.
